Two people including a traffic police officer died in an road accident along Eldoret-Webuye highway on Saturday morning. The accident involved two fuel trucks. The co-driver of the truck and a traffic officer were crashed to death at Kaburengu junction in Kakamega County. Western Region Traffic Commander Geoffrey Njogu said&nbsp;the first truck lost control after its breaks failed before hitting another truck from behind. The driver is recuperating at the Webuye Sub-County Hospital. -Silah Koskei READ MORE NTSA warns against speed gadgets tampering